Name: Muscat
Description: Muscat (Arabic: مسقط) has been inhabited since at least 1000 BCE and for centuries was an important trading port on the Maritime Silk Road. Today it is the capital of the Sultanate of Oman and its most important and populous city (at 812,000). It is home to a multi-ethnic and multi-cultural society, and receives the largest number of foreign visitors to the country.

Name: Bahla
Description: Bahla is a fortified oasis town in Northern Oman, best known for its immense 14th-century fortress and for a unique style of pottery.

Name: Buraimi
Description: Buraimi (Buraymi) is a town in Northern Oman and the capital of the Al Buraymi governate.

Name: Ibra
Description: Ibra is a city in Central Coastal Oman. It's located on the road from Nizwa to Sur and is the gateway to the desert of the Wahiba Sands.

Name: Matrah
Description: Muscat (Arabic: مسقط) has been inhabited since at least 1000 BCE and for centuries was an important trading port on the Maritime Silk Road. Today it is the capital of the Sultanate of Oman and its most important and populous city (at 812,000). Name: Nizwa
Description: Nizwa is a historic city in Northern Oman.

Name: Salalah
Description: Salalah is the capital city of Oman's southern Dhofar region. It is the second largest city in the Sultanate, and has the distinction of being the Sultan Qaboos' birthplace.

Name: Sohar
Description: Sohar is a city in Northern Oman, 100 km north of Muscat.

Name: Sur
Description: Sur is a city in Central Coastal Oman, best known for its dhow shipyards.

Name: Hajar Mountains
Description: The Hajar Mountains are a range in Northern Oman stretching along the northern coast of Oman, from southwest of Muscat to the United Arab Emirates.

Name: Madha
Description: Madha is an exclave of Oman that is completely surrounded by the Fujairah emirate of the United Arab Emirates.

Name: Masirah Island
Description: Masirah Island is in Central Coastal Oman.

Name: Musandam Peninsula
Description: The Musandam Peninsula (Arabic: جَـزِيـرَة مُـسَـنْـدَم‎, Jazīraṫ Musandam) is an exclave of Northern Oman. Musandam is the northernmost tip of a peninsula that juts northward into the Persian Gulf and is roughly divided along its length between Oman and the UAE.

Name: Wahiba Sands
Description: Wahiba Sands is a vast sand dune filled desert just south of Sur in Central Coastal Oman.
